## User Requirements
The user requirements have been categorized based on the system functions they describe:
User Core Identity and Dependencies

* Each User must have exactly one Profile, which is existence-dependent on the User.
* A User must be able to have zero or more Contact methods, which are also existence-dependent on the User.
* Each User must own at least one Vehicle to maintain an active account status.

Vehicle and Booking Management

* The system must allow a User to own and manage one or more Vehicles.
* The system must ensure every Booking is associated with exactly one User and exactly one specific Vehicle.
* The system must allow a User or Vehicle to exist in the system without any past or future Bookings.

Location and Service Operations

* Each Booking must be hosted at exactly one Location.
* Each Location must manage one or more Schedule slots to be available for service.
* A Booking must consist of one or more Services (e.g., Basic Wash, Wax, Interior).
* The system must allow Services to exist in the catalog even if they have not been assigned to any Bookings.

Authentication and Session Management

* The system must ensure that every User has exactly one associated Auth record for credentials, and vice versa.
* The system must allow between one and five active Sessions for a given Auth record at any time.
* The system must allow an Auth record to exist without any active Sessions.

Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

* The system must support many-to-many relationships between Users and Roles, and Roles and Permissions.
* The system must not allow a User to exist without a Role assigned.
* The system must allow a Role to exist without a User assigned.
* The system must allow a Role to exist without any Permissions granted.
* The system must allow a Permission to exist without being assigned to a Role.

